      "raw_text": "A silver medal contest will be held\nat the Pilgrim Congregational church\nFriday, September 4. under the aus\npices Of the w. G. T. u, Mrs. Mary\ns. Trowbridge superintendent. There\nwill be vocal solos by Leonard Olson.\nOscar J. Sand and Miss Litta M. An\nderson and the following recitations:\n\n\n\"A Temperance Story\" Miss Kate\nStorms; \"a Vision of Darkness and\nOf Light\" Nat Purviance; \"a Dream\"\nMiss Marcia Lever; Licensed to\nSell\" Miss Celia Kernfeldt; Result\nOf Treating\" Miss Olive McPhes;\nFarmer Deans Conversion\" Miss\nNellie Bentley: \"Vulture Of Civiliza-\ntion.\" Anthony Koenis; \"Old Soapy.\"\nMiss Louise Quesneiie; 1.-TWO yaga-\nbonds\" Miss r. Grace Long."
